description:
This is a 11 minute workout called 'Wim Hof Method Guided Breathing for Beginners (3 Rounds Slow Pace)' from the channel Wim Hof.
The workout falls under Rest/Breathing exercises.
It's suitable for Beginner and Intermediate fitness levels.
The workout has a The Deep Recharge and The Zen Flow vibe.
The technique difficulty is Beginner.
The effort required is Light.

Original workout description: !! Don't do the breathing exercises in a swimming pool, before going underwater, beneath the shower, or piloting any vehicle. Always practice sitting or lying down in a safe environment. Tinnitus symptoms may appear as a result of pushing too forcefully during the breathing exercise. If this happens, take a step back in your future practice, itâ€™s important to increase gradually, not forcefully !!

This is a slower paced Wim Hof Method breathing exercise that starts with a 30 seconds hold building up to 90 seconds breath hold. Very suitable for beginners or anyone who prefers a more gentle guidance. 

Safety: Read about Shallow Water Blackout:
https://www.wimhofmethod.com/what-is-shallow-water-blackout
